<TITLE> 23 killed in lightning </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 2 (bdnews24.com)  At least 23 people were killed in nine districts and scores other injured in lightning on Saturday and Sunday. Of them, 21 were killed on Sunday and others on Saturday. Most of them were farmers working in the fields. bdnews24.com correspondents reported that five of them were killed in Habiganj, four in Bagerhat, three in Moulvibazar, three in Mymensingh, two each in Narayanganj and Chandpur, and one each in Gaibandha and Satkhira on Sunday. On Saturday, one was killed in Gaibandha and one in Nilphamari. A number of people were also injured in lightning during the storm. b
